args:
The party completes the gate and prevents the
destruction of their world. However, the gate is
unstable, leaving everyone with only moments
to reflect on how their bonds of friendship have
strengthened before returning to their own
home worlds.
*pant* *pant* Still more are coming...\nHow much longer can we— Huh?!
The rifts are starting to close...\nThey must have finished the gate!
Well done, Heroes. Even in the face of\nmy army, you managed to stave off the\ndestruction of your world. Impressive.

Yeah, ain't that just like a loser to pretend
they never cared about their plan in the
first place once they're beaten. Next you'll
claim ya wanted to lose the whole time!
Not at all. And even if it were the case,\nit is the place of humanity to overturn\nthe best-laid schemes of the gods.
For the sake of your ideals do you\ndefy and resist us. Such strength is\na treasure we do not possess.
Your strength has earned my respect,\nand thus I shall withdraw.
Stay, coward! Stay, and let our battle\nbe settled for all time this day!
All will be finished in due time,\nfor we are destined to meet again\nin a world far from this one.
So this is the new gate, eh?
It is a makeshift structure at best;\nI do not know how long it will hold.
Nevertheless, it should suffice for getting\nus back to our world. Thank you, everyone.\nWe never could have done it without you.
And now, let us go home.
Wait, already?! Surely we've earned\na bit of time to kick up our heels!
The gate is not stable, Sharena.\nWe must return while its power yet holds.
If the gate were to lose power,\nour abilities would resume harming\nthis realm.
I suppose I can't argue with that.
Man, you guys always leave the party\nbefore it can even get started!

Don't be sad, for we can meet again
whenever you like. All you need to do
is close your eyes, and you will be in
the realm of dreams.
You can always find me there!
In that case, I'll hop the sleepytrain\nto snoozetown and come see ya!
So long, Tiki. Be well, wherever you go.
I'm so happy I got to meet someone\nelse like me, Mym!
Your world may be a lonely one with so\nfew dragons, but never forget...
In this world, you have a great\nmany friends who care about you.
Yay! I'm not going to be lonely anymore!
Prince Chrom, I owe you a debt of\ngratitude. Were it not for you, this \nworld might have been destroyed.
Save your thanks for your sister, Zethia.\nI merely did as she asked.
To think one day it would be me who\ntraveled back in time to change the\nfuture... Life is full of strange turns indeed.
But thank you again for all you have done.\nYou proved that with trusted allies at one's\nside, even destiny can be overcome.
Do you recall the last time we parted,\nPrince {player_name}?
You said that due to the strength of the\nbonds we forged, you knew we would see\neach other again—and you were right.
And I'm happy we did, even if it\nwas for such a short time.
This wasn't quite the reunion I'd been\nhoping for, but I suppose I'll take it.
Well, let me just throw this out there,\nbut in no way do I believe that this is\ngoing to be our final parting.
After all, I still have so many more\nfriends to make on this world!
And if you want to talk about ＂forging\nbonds,＂ you and I forged a huge one!
Which means WE get to meet up again\nsomewhere down the line too, right?
Now look, Sharena. You've left Prince\n{player_name} all tongue-tied.
Sorry about that. She's always putting\nwords in my mouth as well.
It's all right. My sister Zethia used to\ndo the same thing, once...
You've nothing to be sorry for. If anything,\nwhat happened has given me more\nconfidence that I can get her back.
Even in her current form, she managed to\nsave my life; there is every reason to\nhope that the Other can be beaten.
You've got this. I know it. So next time\nI visit, I'll hang out with you AND Zethia.
ALL of us are going to meet again!
I also believe the bonds we forged\nwill bring us together once more.\nBut for now, farewell, everyone!
And until that day, don't any of you\ndare forget about me!
